name: Brian Frosh
tweet: If you receive a call from a loved one stuck in a bad situation and pleading for money, are you sure it’s actually them? This is a common scam to steal money. Hang up the phone and call the loved one yourself. If they don’t answer, call someone you KNOW to verify what’s going on.  https://t.co/YySGn5ZCOP

tweet: Despite current law, pregnant workers are not fully protected in their jobs. name: Brian Frosh
tweet: There are three tactics scammers love to use when trying to defraud you through email: fear, urgency, and curiosity. Unsolicited, intimidating emails are most likely scams. Ignore, delete, and block. Don’t let a phishing attempt ruin your holidays.  https://t.co/5T5NSxQFAW

name: Brian Frosh
tweet: Biometrics are a way for digital devices to recognize your identity based on physical characteristics (e.g., fingerprint as a password).
